data.title: Madison Libraries
data.text: A documentary film focusing on the political demonstrations in Madison, Wis., protesting the Vietnam War. News footage, interviews, and U.S. Army footage illustrate the development of the anti-war movement in America. VBA 226 is the version of the film that aired on PBS. VBA 227 is a "Postscript" that followed the airing on PBS. The "Postscript" includes interviews with people involved in the protests and shows Carl Anderson's release from prison.
